    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-18T01:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-18T01:54:00-05:00" n="870"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Moose, James/439: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-18T10:00:00+03:06"
                            >July 18, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Reference is made to the Department’s instruction of June 10 [<hi
                        rend="italic">14</hi>], 1943.<note n="6" xml:id="d870fn6">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Kirk’s letter of recall and my letter of credence were presented to Amir Faisal
                    as Viceroy<note n="7" xml:id="d870fn7">The Amir, a son of King Ibn Sand, was
                        also Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> today. Forms executed.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Cairo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
